<p>The footer pattern demonstrates the information that should be found at the bottom of all pages.</p>

<p>There are two components of the footer: the <code>copyright-footer</code> and <code>navigation-menu-footer</code>. The <code>copyright-footer</code> contains copyright, legal information and social media links. The <code>navigation-menu-footer</code> contains links and contact information relevant to the website.</p>

<h2>Usage</h2>

<ul>
	<li>The <code>copyright-footer</code> must appear at the bottom of all pages without any modifications.</li>
    <li>The <code>navigation-menu-footer</code> should be used if needed and should contain content relevant to the section of the website where the page is located.</li>
    <li>The <code>navigation-menu-footer</code> must never be included without the <code>copyright-footer</code> below it.</li>
    <li>The third column in the <code>navigation-menu-footer</code> must be reserved for the contact information.</li>
    <li>Custom icons for social media links must not be added. Unique social media links must use text and can only be added to the <code>navigation-menu-footer</code> (see example below).</li>
</ul>
